Place @boneless pork shoulder butt roast{4%lbs} in a slow cooker.  Add @root beer or cola{1%can} (12 oz.).  Cook, covered, on low until meat is tender: 8 - 10 hours.
Remove roast; cool slightly.  Discard cooking juices.  Shred pork with two forks; return to slow cooker.  Stir in @barbecue sauce{18%oz}.  Cook, covered, until heated through, about 30 minutes.  Serve on rolls or buns.